The paper deals with the problem of 1-bit compressive sampling, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The optimization model and algorithm proposed in the paper involve techniques from machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm in terms of signal recovery, which is a topic related to statistical inference (cs.SI).
